&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13013267/13013267_tesseract_exe.PNG&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17211112" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2020 15:56:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for opening this.  The reason we do this is to defend against command injections.  We could make the regex much more general &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-_\+A-Za-z0-9&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;+ and achieve the same goal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
